channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Kamala Harris Tyrannical 2019 Video Resurfaces: 'I Will Snatch Their Patent So That We Will Take Over'
Florida GOP lawmaker wants to ban smoking on streets, but supports legalizing marijuana
item.description: Smoking and vaping in public in Florida may soon be a thing of the past if a bill by Florida GOP sate Sen. Joe Gruters becomes law. The bill would be introduced if weed in the state is legalized.

item.title: Rasmussen Poll: Majority Say Media in Tank for Harris
item.description: Nearly 6 in 10 likely voters say the media is shilling for Democrat presidential nominee Kamala Harris, with exactly 60% saying reporters try to help the candidate they want to win, according to a new Rasmussen Reports poll released Friday.

item.title: Legal Pundits Warn of 'October Surprise' for Trumpâ€”in September
Democratic National Convention: Biden, Obama, Clintons to address the party ahead of Harris' nomination
item.description: Top Democrats, including President Biden and former presidents are headed to Chicago for the Democratic National Convention to celebrate the nomination of Vice President Kamala Harris.

item.title: Harris Agrees to Meet With Teamsters
item.description: Kamala Harris' campaign said Friday the vice president has accepted an invitation to meet with the International Brotherhood of Teamsters.

item.title: Feel-Good Friday: Emmy Eaton Infuses Joy and Curiosity Into '7 Questions With Emily'
Biden-Harris admin says crime is down, but independent data shows violent crime up across 66 cities
item.description: Despite the Biden-Harris White House's claims of reduced violent crime under their administration, reports show rising crime rates compared to pre-COVID levels.

item.title: Lewandowski to Newsmax: Dem Ticket 'Most Dangerous' Ever
item.description: Corey Lewandowski, campaign manager for Donald Trump in 2016 who recently rejoined the former president's team for this year's race, told Newsmax the Democrat ticket of Vice President Kamala Harris and Minnesota Gov. Tim Walz is "the most dangerous our country has ever seen."

item.title: NEW: Supreme Court Denies Biden Admin. Emergency Request to Partially Reinstate Title IX Rule
'We've got their back': GOP nominee in key Senate race touts support for working class voters
item.description: Former Rep. Mike Rogers, the Republican Senate nominee in battleground Michigan, speaks one-on-one with Fox News Digital as he spotlights a populist message.

item.title: FBI Fires Back at Charge of Obstruction in Butler Probe
item.description: The FBI on Friday fired back at the Republican lawmaker who accused the agency of obstruction in Congress' investigation into the assassination attempt on former President Donald Trump, calling the accusation "inaccurate and unfounded."

item.title: There's a Truly Awesome New Ad for Trump...Featuring a Little Help From Kamala
Newsom signs package to curb smash-and-grab robberies, car thefts
item.description: California Gov. Gavin Newsom signed a bipartisan package of 10 bills in an attempt to reduce smash-and-grab robberies and property crimes in the state.

item.title: Matt Schlapp to Newsmax: Harris Can't Escape Biden's Shadow
item.description: By not giving President Joe Biden a prime speaking spot at the Democratic National Convention, Vice President Kamala Harris shows she is trying to distance herself as much as possible from the administration's poor policies, Matt Schlapp told Newsmax on Friday.
